{
  "stem": "18486.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I was-- yeah, then I was married, and-- yeah, I remember that a lot of-- I-- I remember that first of all, a lot of Jewish people came to Holland, and that they had a terrible shock when the Germans invaded our country.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- most of them-- many of them tried to flee to England.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Certainly, and [LAUGHS] everybody who had a boat, or could get near a boat, went.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because that was not such a far trip, not even to England.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the ones who were-- stayed in Holland, started to hide.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we had a lot of Jewish people in our house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "By that time I was married.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was married to my second husband.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I still had-- my first husband was German.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so in Holland, when a young girl in Holland-- or a woman in Holland-- marries a foreigner, she loses her-- in that time-- her nationality.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 152,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I became a German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 153,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And even when I was divorced, and married my Dutch husband, I still was German.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 153,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because I could not apply, because it was in the war that I married.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 153,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I couldn't apply because I couldn't attract any attention to us, because we had so many Jewish people hidden.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 154,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, German citizen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 155,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, all my friends and everybody I knew, my family, knew that I was not an alien, but--",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 156,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And other people didn't know, I mean, I didn't tell it around, I am German.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 157,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 157,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because I had a-- for instance, we had distribution cards.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 157,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I got double distribution cards, because I was German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 157,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was wonderful, because I could help the Jewish people with that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 158,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't get the-- they didn't get the distribution cards.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
